track_notes: First forrest road. Then a small trail

I have picked this trail because on the map it looked shorter than the route described by LA1ENA. I DO NOT RECOMMEND THIS ROUTE because there is an overgrown steep section where the forest road ends at about 250m asl. The track for the descent follows LA1ENAs description and this is the better route also for ascent. I have uploaded this track to prevent others from the same error in taking what looks like a shorter route on the map. 

We found plenty of blueberries and raspberries which summes up the nice part of this hike.
track_title: from the small town of Eltvet - NOT RECOMMENDED

track_notes:
We found a nice parking space next to an electric transformer station.

The track shown here is our descent, but I recommend this route also for the ascent. It starts with a long hike on a forest service road. There is a short boggy section where you leave the road and cross through the valley to the westside of the mountain. From there follow an unmarked trail to the summit.

The summit area is a huge, flat plateau covered in pine trees and no view in any direction, but plenty of space for antennas!
